  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 240&deg;C/ 220&deg;C (fan)/ 475&deg;F/ Gas 9</p>\r\n<p>Cut the <strong>potatoes</strong> (skins on) into wedges</p>\r\n<p>Add the <strong>wedges</strong> to a baking tray skin-side down (to prevent sticking) with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> and season generously with <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong></p>\r\n<p>Put the tray in the oven for 30 min or until the potatoes are golden</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/162__step-1-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/162__step-1-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/162__step-1-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/162__step-1-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/162__step-1-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, drain and grate the <strong>beetroot</strong> into a sieve (over a bowl), then press and squeeze to release any excess juice (you'll use this later!)</p>\r\n<p>Season the <strong>grated beetroot</strong> generously with <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong></p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/162__step-2-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/162__step-2-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/162__step-2-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/162__step-2-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/162__step-2-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Chop the <strong>tarragon</strong> finely, including the stalks</p>\r\n<p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) the <strong>garlic</strong></p>\r\n<p>Combine the <strong>grated beetroot</strong>, <strong>oats</strong>, <strong>garlic</strong> and <strong>egg<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong>&nbsp;with half of the <strong>chopped&nbsp;</strong><strong>tarragon</strong> (you'll use the rest later) and mix well to combine thoroughly</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/162__step-3-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/162__step-3-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/162__step-3-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/162__step-3-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/162__step-3-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Make 2 <span class=\"text-danger\">[4]</span>&nbsp;<strong>patties</strong> from the burger mix, squeeze them until they hold their shape, then place in the fridge to firm up</p>\r\n<p>Meanwhile, peel and finely slice the <strong>red&nbsp;</strong><strong>onion<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/162__step-4-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/162__step-4-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/162__step-4-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/162__step-4-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/162__step-4-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with 1-2 tbsp <strong>olive oil</strong> over a medium-high heat</p>\r\n<p>Once hot, add the <strong>sliced&nbsp;</strong><strong>onion</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and cook for 5 min until the onion has softened slightly</p>\r\n<p>Reduce the heat to medium-low, add the reserved <strong>beetroot juice</strong> and cook for a further 5 min or until caramelised</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/162__step-5-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/162__step-5-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/162__step-5-x700.jpg",
